I

Image - Class in org.sikuli.script
This class hides the complexity behind image names given as string.
Its companion is ImagePath that maintains a list of places, where images are stored.
Another companion is ImageGroup allowing to to look at images in a folder as a group.
An Image object:
- has a name, either given or taken from the basename without ending.
- keeps its in memory buffered image in a configurable cache avoiding reload from source
- remembers, where it was found the last time searched
- can be sourced from the filesystem, from jars, from the web and from other in memory images
- it will have features for basic image manipulation
- it contains the stuff to communicate with the underlying OpenCV based search engine
This class maintains
- a list of all images loaded with there source reference and a ref to the image object
- a list of all images currently storing their in memory buffered image (managed as a cache)

ImageGroup - Class in org.sikuli.script
An ImageGroup object represents images, that are all in the same folder.
the folder can contain a set of sub folders that can be switched dynamically
The folder will be found on the image path.
The match data of the images can be stored and reloaded.
Its main purpose is to support image sets for different environments.
At runtime you can switch between image sets without changing the used image names.
Based on the stored match data you might produce a new ImageGroup on the fly.

Screen - Class in org.sikuli.script
A screen represents a physical monitor with its coordinates and size according to the global point system: the screen areas are grouped around a point (0,0) like in a cartesian system (the top left corner and the points contained in the screen area might have negative x and/or y values)
The screens are arranged in an array (index = id) and each screen is always the same object (not possible to create new objects).
Screen(int) - Constructor for class org.sikuli.script.Screen
